imension comprise a separate ai rmf audience who informs the primary audience\",\"as a result the best intentions within one dimension of the ai lifecycle can be undermined via interactions with decisions and conditions in other later activities\",\"when identifying whether ai is the right solution its important that you work with specialists who have a good knowledge of your data and the problem youre trying to solve such as data scientists\",\"ai system dependency and reliance on data for training tasks combined with increased volume and complexity typically associated with such data\",\"map  information about the ai systems knowledge limits and how system output may be utilized and overseen by humans is documented\",\"costs consider how much it will cost to build run and maintain an ai infrastructure train and educate staff and if the work to install ai may outweigh any potential savings\",\"ai a branch of computer science is complex and evolving in terms of its precise definition\",\"manage  mechanisms are in place and applied to sustain the value of deployed ai systems\",\"the ai rmf functions described in section  require diverse perspectives disciplines professions and experiences\",\"however ai systems generally require large amounts of data\",\"introductionartificial intelligence ai systems are poised to have a significant impact on the lives of canadians and the operations of canadian businesses\",\"ai can be defined as the use of digital technology to create systems capable of performing tasks commonly thought to require intelligence\",\"end users of an ai system are the individuals or groups that use the system for specific purposes\",\"here the semantic difference between people in aggregate and individual persons is of importance\",\"different ai actors have different responsibilities and awareness depending on their roles in the lifecycle\",\"ai systems as well as the ecosystems in which they are deployed may be said to be resilient if they can withst