d buy or collaborate allocate responsibility for ai models assess your existing data build your ai team get your data ready for ai and plan your ai modelling phase\",\"keeping your teams first model simple and setting up the right end to end infrastructure will help smooth the transition from alpha to beta\",\"first the prediction service provider decides how to create and train the model that powers its services and processes data for these purposes\",\"whether the model shows any signs of bias\",\"architectural details of how models will be deployed such as the choice of virtual machines microservices apis\",\"membership inference attacks allow malicious actors to deduce whether a given individual was present in the training data of a ml model\",\"a proprietary model was developed to predict the likelihood of sepsis in hospitalized patients and was implemented at hundreds of hospitals around the country\",\"so even if you dont use protected characteristics in your model it is very possible that you may inadvertently use a model which has detected patterns of discrimination based on those protected characteristics and is reproducing them in its outputs\",\"if you have created a model yourself has the intended use of the model been clearly communicated to ensure that it is not misused\",\"ai development tasks are performed during the ai model phase of the lifecycle\",\"identification and classification while the supervisory authorities do not currently provide an explicit definition of a model the pra proposed definition is being consulted on in cp the pra expects that banks should give consideration to what factors would constitute a model and must establish their own definition of a model and furthermore banks should maintain a model inventory with clear information regarding but not limited to owners users uses and direct or material dependencies see pra ss model risk management principles for stress testing\",\"however this should be done with care and only after careful consideration as deletion of some data may make the model worse or less transparent for the user\",\"plan and prototype your ai model build and service\",\"alpha build and evaluate your machine learning model\",\"even models which are not overfitted to the training data can still be vulnerable to privacy attacks\",\"a query is sent to the ml model containing the predictor variables for a new instance eg a new customers age income occupation\",\"evaluating your model undertake continuous evaluation to make sure the model still meets business objectives and the model is performing at the level required\",\"your team will need to test your models throughout the process to mitigate against issues such as overfitting or underfitting that could undermine your models effectiveness once deployed\",\"whilst developers cannot stop others from using their models to remain accountable anyone making and training models should try to be explicit in communicating the intended use of a model so that models are not created that are then used by others in the wrong way\",\"the extent to which poor model performance leads to poor outcomes can depend on the degree of autonomy of a model\",\"this will make sure the model performance is in line with the modelling phase and to help you identify when to retrain the model\",\"for example some ai providers give third parties an entire pre trained model and allow them to run it locally\",\"when you complete building your ai prototyping phase you should have a final model or set of predictive models and a summary of their performance and characteristics\",\"integration can happen in a number of ways from a local deployment to the creation of a custom application for staff or customers\",\"the programmer will reward the machine when it does what the programmer wants and penalise it when it does not though the programmer will not give the models help in making these decisions\",\"how and when you will evaluate the model\",\"what level of performance you need before deploying the model\",\"in addition to ongoing cost youll need to think about the network and memory resources your team will need to train your model\",\"this will depend on a number of factors including the intended use of the model the maintainability of the model and its outputs and whether using the more transparent alternative risks sacrificing the quality or accuracy of another more opaque model\",\"when choosing your final model you will need to consider what level of performance your problem needs\",\"at least one domain knowledge expert who knows the environment where you will be deploying the ai model results\",\"in some cases ml model providers and clients will be joint controllers and therefore need to perform a joint risk assessment\",\"this is because even if these variables are excluded from the model they could still be correlated from other data points and identify protected characteristics\",\"one possible cause of ml models being vulnerable to privacy attacks is known as overfitting\",\"step  firm a uses this model to develop a high impact system by training it on data under their control and then place it on the market for use  firm a would need to comply with the requirements for development and making available for use which would be laid out in regulation eg testing ensuring that all measures needed for safe and fair operation are in place providing documentation to firms purchasing the system\",\"as the model provider you will be less easily able to monitor the model during deployment and thereby assess and mitigate the risk of privacy attacks on it\",\"if you are operating as a controller your contract with the processor must stipulate that the processor assist you in responding to rights requests\",\"you also need to take care to identify and understand controller  processor relationships\",\"these two approaches correspond to different operational models\",\"as described above in the initial research and development phase of your ai system your purposes may be quite broad but as more specific purposes are identified you may need to review your lia accordingly or identify a different lawful basis\",\"this test will provide you with the most accurate impression of how your model will perform once deployed\",\"once you have a baseline model your team can start prototyping more complex models\",\"domain expert who knows the environment where you will be deploying the ai model results for example if the model will be investigating social care collaborate with a social worker\",\"you can consider whether the model solves the problem identified\",\"you may not be able to tell if your model is doing this just by looking at the data that went into the model and the outputs that it produces\",\"using your model in your service has three stages\",\"safe operation of ai systems is improved through responsible design development and deployment practices\",\"as the aippf final report noted backup and remediation actions being considered before the model is put into production can enable firms to respond appropriately and in a timely manner if an ai model performance or output deteriorates beyond the accepted risk threshold which can help manage risks\",\"similar to the earlier frt example membership inference attacks can exploit confidence scores provided alongside a models prediction\",\"the model then will try to maximise its reward causing it to change its decisions strategise\",\"your team will need to train the models they build on data\",\"frt systems are often designed to allow third parties to query the model\",\"create a baseline model\",\"how any models will be continuously tested and updated how often using what kinds of data and how ongoing performance will be assessed\",\"preparing your data for an ai model\",\"it would be useful to consider whether the models are achieving their purpose and business objectives\",\"deployment how should the performance of live ai systems be monitored\",\"your risk management policies should clearly set out both the process and the person responsible for the final validation of an ml system both before deployment and where appropriate after an update\",\"if you are going to provide a whole model to others via an application programming interface api you will not be subject to white box attacks in this way because the apis users will not have direct access to the model itself\",\"how the data and models are stored such as the formats they are serialised and stored in and local caching\",\"the gravity of the consequences of models vulnerability to membership inference will depend on how sensitive or revealing membership might be\",\"datasets used to train ai systems may become detached from their original and intended context or may become stale or outdated relative to deployment context\",\"your team should build a simple baseline version model before they build any more complex models\",\"you can consider whether there is a clear and accountable owner of the model\",\"build a prototype of the model and service\",\"decisions that go into the design development deployment evaluation and use of ai systems reflect systemic and human cognitive biases\",\"ai deployment actors are responsible for contextual decisions relating to how the ai system is used to assure deployment of the system into production\",\"ai systems should be tested before their deployment and regularly while in operation\",\"include engineers early in the building of the ai model to make sure any code developed is production ready\",\"you cannot integrate the model\",\"as we review our cloud computing guidance we will consult on the scenarios which could result in an organisation becoming a controller which may include when organisations make decisions about the source and nature of the data used to train an ai model\",\"ai development actors provide the initial infrastructure of ai systems and are responsible for model building and interpretation tasks which involve the creation selection calibration training andor testing of models or algorithms\",\"questions for you to consider with data scientists are do you have enough data for the model to learn from\",\"using a pre existing model with the same intended use as a basis for your project may save time and money\",\"feature selection  the features that may be used in each model\",\"once you select a final model your team will need to assess its performance and refine it to make sure it performs as well as you need it to\",\"include reasonable features processes and analytical structures in your model architecture design fairness\",\"responsible decision making by deployers and end users\",\"you can action this by focusing on the infrastructure requirements for your ai pipelines as the same time your team is developing the model\",\"your team should split your data into a training set to train algorithms during the modelling phase validation set for assessing the performance of your models test set for a final check on the performance of your best model\",\"for example an ml model could be installed on the users own device and make inferences locally rather than being hosted on a cloud server\",\"in white box attacks the attacker has complete access to the model itself and can inspect its underlying code and properties although not the training data\",\"how it performs compared to simpler models\",\"for any given ai system an ai designer or developer may have a different perception of the characteristics than the deployer\",\"building verification and validation task and output eg\",\"include reasonable features processes and analytical structures in your model architecture design fairness\",\"in these cases unauthorised parties may be able to recover elements of the training data or infer who was in it by analysing the way the model behaves\",\"in these cases a small set of individual examples are contained somewhere in the internal logic of the model\",\"higher degree of difficulty in predicting failure modes for emergent properties of large scale pre trained models\",\"the inference phase when the model is used to make a prediction or classification about new instances\",\"when assessing your models performance consider\",\"launched a private beta followed by a public end to end beta prototype which users can use in full\",\"tevv tasks for design planning and data may center on internal and external validation of assumptions for system design data collection and measurements relative to the intended context of deployment or application\",\"an ai service provider isolates different client specific models\",\"its useful to consider how youll manage data collection pipelines to support reliable model performance and a clean input for modelling such as batch upload or continuous upload\",\"how interpretable you need your model to be\",\"test the model and service\",\"the target output of the model what is being predicted or classified\",\"beta deploy and maintain your model\",\"who will maintain the model\",\"moving from alpha to beta involves integrating the model into the services decision making process and using live data for the model to make predictions on\",\"moreover the proposed principles cover all elements of the model lifecycle and would be applicable to all types of models that are used to inform key business decisions whether developed in house or externally including vendor models and models used for financial reporting purposes\",\"for example the product offers a customer sees on a website might be driven by the output of the predictive model stored in their profile\",\"the complexity of the organisation deploying it\",\"using pre trained models may be particularly problematic if the model lacks transparency as it may be harder to identify the processes used to train the model and existing biases\",\"designers and implementers of ai systems should be able toexplain to affected stakeholders how and why a model performed the way it did in a specific context\",\"there is an important distinction between black box and white box attacks on models\",\"key model parameters eg how complex a decision tree can be or how many models will be included in an ensemble\",\"you should continue to collect user needs so your team can use the models outputs in the real world\",\"keep this data separate from your models until this final test\",\"for example models may become correlated in subtle ways and add to risks of herding or procyclical behaviour at times of market stress\",\"step  a researcher at a university publishes a new model that can be used to develop ai systems  no regulatory requirements or liability under aida as it is not a commercial activity and the model alone is not a complete ai system\",\"in addition it is possible to train an ml model using a programming language and framework suitable for exploratory development but then convert the model into another more secure format for deployment\",\"model validation and independent review the validation and independent review of an ai model is important in order to ensure an objective view is given on the model inclusive of the way in which it is developed and that it is suitable for the intended purpose\",\"while it is not a legal requirement having a well organised model management system and deployment pipeline will make it easier and cheaper to accommodate these requests and re training and redeploying your ai models accordingly will be less costly\",\"this will give you an indication of how your model will perform in the real world\",\"evaluate the model\",\"if you are considering using a pre trained model it is important to understand what the model was built to be used for and ensure before it is implemented that it is suitable for your own project\",\"if you are using a pre existing model have you ensured that you are using it in the way it was intended\",\"you should regularly assess drift and retrain the model on new data where necessary\",\"justifiable prioritise the transparency of how you design and implement your model and the justification and interpretability of its decisions and behaviours\",\"after creating a beta version you team can use automated testing to create some high level tests before moving to more thorough testing\",\"it may be useful to discuss your project with independent colleagues as part of challenge sessions both to maximise collective understanding and to provide an additional opportunity to check the model is doing what is expected\",\"model uses and impacts\",\"make sure your model is fair explainable and you have a process for monitoring unexpected or biased outputs\",\"as part of your accountability responsibilities you should decide and document appropriate thresholds for determining whether your model needs to be retrained based on the nature scope context and purposes of the processing and the risks it poses\",\"in a model inversion attack if attackers already have access to some personal data belonging to specific individuals included in the training data they can infer further personal information about those same individuals by observing the inputs and outputs of the ml model\",\"the nature of the hyperparametersfootnote functional form of the models and their outputs can also adapt continuously\",\"if you are operating an ai service as a joint controller you need to decide with your fellow controllers who will carry out which obligations\",\"white and black box attacks can be performed by providers customers or anyone else with either authorised or unauthorised access to either the model itself or its query or response functionality\",\"the cost of maintaining the model\",\"that might be contained in the model itself\",\"white box attacks enable additional information to be gathered such as the type of model and parameters used which could help an attacker in inferring personal data from the model\",\"however you remain responsible for assessing and mitigating the risk that personal data used to train your models may be exposed as a result of the way your clients have deployed the model\",\"a monitoring framework to evaluate the models performance and rapidly identify incidents\",\"for example failures with the data chosen to train the ai model design of the model coding of the software or deployment\",\"if your model is going to be provided in whole to a third party rather than being merely accessible to them via an api then you will need to consider the risk of white box attacks\",\"utilising models beyond their intended use without care and caution may impact upon the accuracy and validity of your results\",\"by definition they are external to the design development or deployment team of the organization that acquires its technologies or services\",\"tevv tasks for deployment include system validation and integration in production with testing and recalibration for systems and process integration user experience and compliance with existing legal regulatory and ethical specifications\",\"if you train models and provide them to others you should assess whether those models may contain personal data or are at risk of revealing it if attacked and take appropriate steps to mitigate these risks\",\"if you are using machine learning with personal data you should proactively  assess the chances that your model might be inferring protected characteristics or special category data or both in order to make predictions and actively monitor this possibility throughout the lifecycle of the system\",\"the model responds with its best guess as to the target variable for this new instance eg whether or not the new customer will default on a loan\",\"how should ai models be tested before live deployment\",\"the database will be operated by the commission and provided with data by the providers of the ai systems who will be required to register their systems before placing them on the market or otherwise putting them into service\",\"is the data representative of the users the models results will impact\",\"model deployment and people and planet eg\",\"more substantially you may identify a need to collect more or better training data to fill in the gaps that led to the erroneous decision or modify the model building process ie by changing the feature selection\",\"your team will need to evaluate your model to assess how it is performing against unseen data\",\"you need to test and confirm any assumptions made in the design phase once the ai system has been trained and built\",\"an understanding of cloud architecture security scalable deployment and open source tools and technologies\",\"manage  pre trained models which are used for development are monitored as part of ai system regular monitoring and maintenance\",\"whether you build buy or reuse or combine these approaches will depend on a number of considerations including whether the needs youre trying to meet are unique to your organisation or you could fulfil users needs with generic components\",\"you can consider how you will monitor the models performance\",\"when the user opens the news app the days news is sent to the phone and the local model would select the most relevant stories to show to the user based on the user personal habits or profile information which are tracked and stored on the device itself and are not shared with the content provider or app store\",\"these services enable clients to build and run their own models with data they have chosen but using the tools and infrastructure the organisation provides in the cloud\",\"this enables each client to make overarching decisions about their model including whether to further process personal data from their own context to improve their own model\",\"for example if your model is scoring cvs as part of a recruitment exercise and the kinds of skills candidates need in a particular job are likely to change every two years you should anticipate assessing the need to re train your fresh data at least that often\",\"evaluate the model\",\"justifiable prioritise the transparency of how you design and implement your model and the justification and interpretability of its decisions and behaviours\",\"while sharing the gradient derived from a locally trained model presents a lower privacy risk than sharing the training data itself a gradient can still reveal some personal information about the individuals it was derived from especially if the model is complex with a lot of fine grained variables\",\"privacy and cybersecurity risk management considerations and approaches are applicable in the design development deployment evaluation and use of ai systems\",\"this characteristics scope spans from design decisions and training data to model training the structure of the model its intended use cases and how and when deployment post deployment or end user decisions were made and by whom\",\"explicit processes for making gono go system commissioning and deployment decisions\",\"integrating your model performance test the model with live data and integrate it within the decision making workflow\",\"ai deployment tasks are performed during the task and output phase of the lifecycle\",\"robust model development and implementation process a robust model development process ensures models are developed to appropriate standards and use representative data which are important considerations for ai models\",\"procurement tasks are conducted by ai actors with financial legal or policy management authority for acquisition of ai models products or services from a third party developer vendor or contractor\",\"tevv tasks for development ie model building include model validation and assessment\",\"a predictive model marketed as being able to predict whether students are likely to drop out of school was used by more than  universities across the country\",\"understand the processes and how the ai model will connect with the wider service\",\"if the model learns to use particular combinations of features that are sufficiently revealing of a special category then the model may be processing special category data\",\"this model was chosen in careful consideration of a number of factors given the unique ai regulatory context and the objectives of the regulatory scheme\",\"model inversion and membership inference attacks can exploit this\",\"security and ml researchers are still working to understand what factors make ml models more or less vulnerable to these kinds of attacks and how to design effective protections and mitigation strategies\",\"in many cases when determining your purposes and lawful basis it will make sense for you to separate the research and development phase including conceptualisation design training and model selection of ai systems from the deployment phase\",\"how was the model evaluatedcompared against other models\",\"your simple model will provide baseline metrics and information on the models behaviour that you can use to test more complex models\",\"for example you need to do this where the ai system was developed for a general purpose task and you then deploy it in different contexts for different purposes\",\"testing conditions should mirror as closely as possible the conditions in which the system will be deployed and new testing may be required for each deployment to account for material differences in conditions from one deployment to another\",\"limes use a simpler surrogate model to summarise the relationships between input and output pairs that are similar to those in the system you are trying to interpret\",\"iterate and deploy improved models\",\"if it is not feasible to deploy the model locally other privacy enhancing techniques exist to minimise the data that is revealed in a query sent to a ml model\",\"typically once deployed the outputs of an ai system are stored in a profile of an individual and used to take some action about them\",\"if the request is for access to the data you could fulfil this without altering the model\",\"however new types of privacy attacks on ml models suggest that this is sometimes possible\",\"case example a system developed by multiple actorsconsider the case of an ai system with multiple development steps involving both research and commercial activities\",\"avoiding overfitting will help both in mitigating the risk of privacy attacks and also in ensuring that the model is able to make good inferences on new examples it hasnt seen before\",\"simply removing any protected characteristics from the inputs the model uses to make a prediction is unlikely to be enough as there are often variables which are proxies for the protected characteristics\",\"the way the model is deployed eg via a user interface which doesnt meet accessibility requirements\",\"having a secure pipeline from development to deployment will further mitigate security risks associated with third party code by separating the ml development environment from the rest of your it infrastructure where possible\",\"the nist framework will consider and encompass principles such as transparency accountability and fairness during pre design design and development deployment use and testing and evaluation of ai technologies and systems\",\"who will monitor the models performance how often you will assess the model\",\"furthermore for the reasons stated above there may also be situations where your model infers special category as an intermediate step to another non special category data inference\",\"decision possibilities resulting from performance testing should include the possibility of not deploying the system\",\"the clients are controllers as they take the overarching decisions about what data and models they want to use the key model parameters and the processes for evaluating testing and updating those models\",\"differential privacy is a way to measure whether a model created by an ml algorithm significantly depends on the data of any particular individual used to train it\",\"choose the final model\",null],\"marker\":{\"opacity\":0.5,\"size\":5},\"mode\":\"markers+text\",\"name\":\"Developing AI models\",\"text\":[\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"Developing AI models\"],\"textfont\":{\"size\":12},\"x\":[8.573478698730469,9.856663703918457,9.527822494506836,9.516855239868164,4.962766170501709,9.457367897033691,9.549606323242188,9.748186111450195,9.52804183959961,8.52249526977539,9.573305130004883,9.66785717010498,7.604593276977539,8.20838737487793,9.232651710510254,9.00778579711914,4.915261268615723,7.863419055938721,9.497432708740234,9.553506851196289,9.521805763244629,9.502829551696777,9.397408485412598,9.473542213439941,9.38115119934082,9.142571449279785,9.386734962463379,9.466667175292969,9.487669944763184,5.9267354011535645,8.731290817260742,9.406477928161621,9.466512680053711,9.420047760009766,9.078556060791016,9.447131156921387,9.220427513122559,7.116199970245361,8.218435287475586,9.628252029418945,