ual or augmented reality workplace training programs and electronic workplace surveillance and management systems\",\"many of the most popular ml development frameworks are open source\",\"the fca mission sets out a framework for the way the fca takes these decisions and serves the public interest\",\"the powers listed in paragraphs   and  are without prejudice to section\",\"the framework should support organizations abilities to operate under applicable domestic and international legal or regulatory regimes\",\"however at this stage neither have passed through the house or senate and are not likely to come into force in the near future\",\"on the other hand the independence of these authorities should not mean that they cannot be subject in accordance with national constitutions and without endangering the achievement of the objectives of this regulation to national control or monitoring mechanisms regarding their financial expenditure or to judicial review or that they should not have the possibility to consult other national authorities including law enforcement authorities or crisis management authorities where appropriate\",\"governance is designed to be a cross cutting function to inform and be infused throughout the other three functions\",\"an automated signature matching system is used as part of the voting process in many parts of the country to determine whether the signature on a mail in ballot matches the signature on file\",\"indeed the bor explicitly states that it does not constitute binding guidance for the public or federal agencies and therefore does not require compliance while the principles of the bor also are non binding the bor provides guidance on how they can or in some cases already are enforced through federaland state level legislation within particular sectors\",\"this is because these are distinct and separate purposes with different circumstances and risks\",\"the framework is intended to be voluntary rights preserving non sector specific and use case agnostic providing flexibility to organizations of all sizes and in all sectors and throughout society to implement the approaches in the framework\",\"map  targeted application scope is specified and documented based on the systems capability established context and ai system categorization\",\"the alan turing institute calls these the sum values\",\"some of these measures conflict with each other meaning you cannot satisfy all of them at the same time\",\"it does not seek to provide an exhaustive comparison of for instance differences between each jurisdictions political and legal institutions\",\"subrogation would also cover heirs of a deceasedvictim\",\"outcomes in the map function are the basis for the measure and manage functions\",\"the most prevalent in the united states is the access boards section  regulations which are the technical standards for federal information communication technology software hardware and web\",\"it is important to distinguish between the terms algorithm and model as these have specific meanings within financial services regulation\",\"a data science platform is a type of software tool which helps teams connect all of the technology they require across their project workflow speeding up ai deployment and increasing the transparency and oversight over ai models\",\"for example the competition and markets authority cma defines algorithmic systems as shorthand for an automated system at the intersection of algorithms data models processes objectives and people\",\"by contrast the use of decision support tools are not subject to these conditions\",\"rights opportunities or access rights opportunities or access is used to indicate the scoping of this framework\",\"other than in respect of the presumptions it lays down this directive does notharmonise national laws regarding which party has the burden of proof or whichdegree of certainty is required as regards the standard of proof\",\"thus this framework uses a two part test to determine what systems are in scope\",\"compliance with one will not guarantee compliance with the other\",\"aspects of govern especially those related to compliance or evaluation should be integrated into each of the other functions\",\"this is because complexity often corresponds to improved performance and use of ever greater volumes of data\",\"aida additionally would not apply to a government institution nor to systems used for military aims\",\"in order to process it you need a lawful basis under article  as well as a separate condition under article  although these do not have to be linked\",\"despite these similarities there are notable differences between bills c  and c\",\"the alan turing institute calls these the fast track principles\",\"in terms of scope they are limited from two perspectives\",\"this article focuses on the key distinctions between bill c  and bill c\",\"build a process based governance framework\",\"for example the definition of artificial intelligence systems in aida aligns with concepts developed through the oecd that are also represented in the eu ai act\",\"currently technology systems are the responsibility of the smf chief operations function  see the pra rulebook senior management functions part rule  and sup cb systems and controls functions other\",\"bill c  never made it into law in part because a federal election was called in\",\"that said as will be stressed below there are key differences in the way these decentralised approaches are enacted\",\"title xi sets out rules for the exercise of delegation and implementing powers\",\"build a process based governance framework\",\"part   sets out a separate regime for the three intelligence services\",\"the usas approach is characterised by non binding principles voluntary guidance on risk management and the application of existing sectoral legislation rather than the development of new ai specific legislation at the federal level\",\"before turning to the comparative analysis based on the framework categories it is helpful to first provide an overview of the key aims of each jurisdictions approach and to briefly comment on their scope\",\"all this is without prejudice to the existing system and allocation of powers of ex post enforcement of obligations regarding fundamental rights in the member states\",\"the pra and the fca have competition related statutory objectives and are required to have regard to the principle of proportionality when exercising their general functions including when making rules\",\"this context is useful for understanding the rationale and trajectory of each governments approach yet it is beyond the scope of this report\",\"similarly there are categories and subcategories with elements that apply to multiple functions or that logically should take place before certain subcategory decisions\",\"some of these also require additional basis or authorisation in uk law which can be found in schedule  of the dpa\",\"first we outline the methodological approach taken for developing the comparative framework\",\"robustness or generalizability is defined as the ability of a system to maintain its level of performance under a variety of circumstances\",\"because the uk is taking a context based and sector led approach to governance liability varies depending on the particular target of a piece of guidance as well as the regulators specific powers and jurisdiction\",\"this specification of sectoral areas for high risk systems introduces a minor vertical component to the horizontal approach\",\"specifically it was one of the initial drafters of the isoiec dis  standard\",\"the definition should be based on the key functional characteristics of the software in particular the ability for a given set of human defined objectives to generate outputs such as content predictions recommendations or decisions which influence the environment with which the system interacts be it in a physical or digital dimension\",\"for example a collection of non profit organizations and companies have worked together to develop a framework that defines operational approaches to transparency for machine learning systems\",\"the ministers regulatory powers could not be used to investigate the criminal offences discussed in the next section which are true crimes that require criminal intent and are punishable by imprisonment\",\"this framework does not prescribe profile templates allowing for flexibility in implementation\",\"it also sets out the definitions used throughout the instrument\",\"while the system does not directly use information about the applicants religion there might be features in the system which are indirect proxies for religion such as previous occupation or qualifications\",\"passive computing infrastructure is any intermediary technology that does not influence or determine the outcome of decision make or aid in decisions inform policy implementation or collect data or observations including web hosting domain registration networking caching data storage or cybersecurity\",\"these principles find kinship in the fair information practice principles fipps derived from the  report of an advisory committee to the us department of health education and welfare records computers and the rights of citizens\",\"the core is composed of four functions govern map measure and manage\",\"additionally if you are a public authority you can only rely on legitimate interests if you are processing for a legitimate reason other than performing your tasks as a public authority\",\"however one important drawback is that these standard ml frameworks often depend on other pieces of software being already installed on an it system\",\"the alan turing institute calls it a pbg framework\",\"while the treasury board may impose consequences for non compliance this is not the same as the broader enforcement powers under the aida\",\"process based governance framework\",\"this is narrower than the personal information protection and electronic documents acts pipeda application to all organizations that collect use or disclose personal information in the course of commercial activities except where there is substantively similar provincial legislation\",\"it is not the responsibility of the machine or system to be considerate of these ideals\",\"further the aida provides the minister with broad order making powers and audit rights\",\"there are three elements to the legitimate interests lawful basis and it can help to think of these as the three part test\",\"such qualification should not extend however to ai systems intended for purely ancillary administrative activities that do not affect the actual administration of justice in individual cases such as anonymisation or pseudonymization of judicial decisions documents or data communication between personnel administratve tasks or allocations of resources\",\"these governments were chosen for the first stage of this project for two related reasons\",\"this ordering does not represent a value judgement about the desirability of governments approaches\",\"the data used for building an ai system may not be a true or appropriate representation of the context or intended use of the ai system and the ground truth may either not exist or not be available\",\"this means the provisions on automated decision making apply as a result a different range of available lawful bases may apply at the development and deployment stages\",\"the govern function also creates mechanisms for organizations to make their decision making processes more explicit to help counter systemic biases\",\"the minister would not have any influence on whether to prosecute an offence and the public prosecution service of canada would need to determine that a prosecution is in the public interest before it could proceed\",\"the provider as a processor could still decide what programming languages and code libraries those tools are written in the configuration of storage solutions the graphical user interface and the cloud architecture\",\"each of these high level functions is broken down into categories and subcategories\",\"a system awarding benefits changed its criteria invisibly\",\"these functions  govern map measure and manage  are broken down further into categories and subcategories\",\"the framework is intended to be flexible and to augment existing risk practices which should align with applicable laws regulations and norms\",\"in the context of this framework such domains are considered sensitive whether or not the specifics of a system context would necessitate coverage under existing law and domains and data that are considered sensitive are understood to change over time based on societal norms and context\",\"we define hard law as legally binding instruments eg primary and secondary legislation whereas soft law as non binding quasi legal instruments\",\"in the case of federated learning participating organisations may be considered joint controllers even though they dont have access to each others data\",\"set of actionable principles\",\"in this section of the report we structure our comparative analysis around some of the key categories of the framework\",\"in some circumstances application of these principles in whole or in part may not be appropriate given the intended use of automated systems to achieve government agency missions\",\"this decentralised sectoral approach is similar to the sectoral approach of the uk\",\"the framework is a tool that should be used in any project\",\"a large majority of stakeholders agree that legislative gaps exist or that new legislation is needed\",\"the ml framework depends on a number of specialist open source programming libraries which needed to be downloaded on the recruiters it system\",\"both the eu and the canadian approach to risk entail horizontal risk frameworks with some vertical components\",\"the alan turing institute calls it a pbg framework\",\"they include among others systems that predict a persons risk of committing a crime or that automate hiring decisions such as sorting resumes or cvs as defined in annex iii\",\"additionally this framework does not analyze or take a position on legislative and regulatory proposals in municipal state and federal government or those in other countries\",\"in substance the resolutions are complementary in many aspects\",\"however some differ in their stringency\",\"similarly linear relationships where the value of the output increases proportional to the input may be easier to interpret than relationships that are non linear where the output value is not proportional to the input or non monotonic where the output value may increase or decrease as the input increases\",\"the prudential regimes eg solvency ii tend to lay out high level principles on data without prescribing detailed guidelines on their implementation\",\"for example the equality of opportunity monitoring provision mentioned above cannot be relied on in such contexts because the processing is carried out for the purposes of decisions about a particular individual\",\"for instance the equalities and human rights commission has powers to provide guidance on equalities law while the competition and markets authority has powers related to consumer law and competition\",\"the framework explicates how enforcement should be undertaken for non compliance for both institutions and individuals\",\"overall the aida would apply to persons including trusts joint ventures partnerships unincorporated associations and any other legal entities who carry out any of the regulated activities as specified above\",\"if you are processing special categories of data you need both a lawful basis and an additional condition for processing\",\"however we acknowledge that this inclusionexclusion criteria still creates some issues for instance the chances of some draft regulations being passed is higher than others eg\",\"it is therefore appropriate forthis directive to use the same definitions in respect of ai systems providers and users\",\"it also is not determinative of what the us governments position will be in any international negotiation\",\"similarly pra ss algorithmic trading expects firms to define the term algorithm section  as used by the firms in the context of algorithmic trading\",\"it is broadly seen as part of a spectrum of computational and mathematical methodologies that include innovative data analytics and data modelling techniques\",\"federal law has not grown to address the expanding scale of private data collection or of the ability of governments at all levels to access that data and leverage the means of private collection\",\"pra ss algorithmic trading sets out expectations for governance eg cross lines of defence coordination smfs testing with regard to the use of algorithms in the context of trading\",\"however where there are relevant differences between the requirements of the regimes these are explained in the text\",\"process based governance framework\",\"it is important to note that activities such as research or the development of methodologies are not in themselves regulated activities under aida\",\"that framework should therefore be preserved\",\"for example smaller firms would not be expected to have governance structures policies and procedures comparable to those of larger firms with a greater number of employees and a wider range of activities\",\"for example the theory of differential privacy provides a framework for quantifying and minimising trade offs between the knowledge that can be gained from a dataset or statistical model and the privacy of the people in it\",\"these frameworks have some features in common with the ai rmf\",\"some organizations may choose to select from among the categories and subcategories others may choose and have the capacity to apply all categories and subcategories\",\"if so what should the definition be\",\"the framework is divided into two parts\",\"set of actionable principles\",\"however elements of the governance structure should be in place before then\",\"for example not all financial and demographic features will be useful to predict credit risk\",\"additionally the proposal does not amend sector specific legislation or the enforcement and governance mechanisms set thereunder but provides for a horizontal framework to rely on for aspects beyond specific content or subcategories of services regulated in sector specific acts\",\"the former would apply to the private sector while the latter applies to government institutions\",\"thisobjective cannot be sufficiently achieved by the member states because the relevantinternal market obstacles are linked to the risk of unilateral and fragmented regulatorymeasures at national level\",\"in the context of this framework such domains are considered sensitive whether or not the specifics of a system context would necessitate coverage under existing law and domains and data that are considered sensitive are understood to change over time based on societal norms and context\",\"the proposal does not foresee the automatic creation of any additional bodies or authorities at member state level\",\"the alan turing institute calls these the sum values\",\"each of these further applications might require a different lawful basis\",\"title vi sets up the governance systems at union and national level\",\"the aida also exempts the federal government from its application\",\"the proposal sets a robust and flexible legal framework\",\"while the principles are non binding and horizontal the bor provides guidance on how they can be enforced by existing federaland state level sectoral legislation as well as federal agency led activities amongst others\",\"in terms of horizontal components it differentiates between unacceptable risk high risk limited risk minimal or no risk ai systems\",\"first we designed the categories to be sufficiently general to capture a full breadth of approaches eg centralised or decentralised hard or soft law approaches\",\"underserved communities the term underserved communities refers to communities that have been systematically denied a full opportunity to participate in aspects of economic social and civic life as exemplified by the list in the preceding definition of equity the below examples are meant to illustrate the breadth of automated systems that insofar as they have the potential to meaningfully impact rights opportunities or access to critical resources or services should be covered by the blueprint for an ai bill of rights\",\"government applications particularly law enforcement applications or applications that raise national security considerations may require confidential or limited engagement based on system sensitivities and preexisting oversight laws and structures\",\"with all of these definitions it is important to note that while both algorithms and models may be components of an ai system they may not in themselves necessarily be deemed to be ai\",\"for banks the general organisational requirements part  states that firms must have robust governance arrangements which include a clear organisational structure with well defined transparent and consistent lines of responsibility and effective control and safeguard arrangements for information processing systems\",\"in some cases more than one lawful basis may be appropriate\",\"map  context is established and understood\",\"assuming a governance structure is in place functions may be performed in any order across the ai lifecycle as deemed to add value by a user of the framework\",null],\"marker\":{\"opacity\":0.5,\"size\":5},\"mode\":\"markers+text\",\"name\":\"Implementing an AI governance Framework\",\"text\":[\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\",\"\"